Property lists can be either online or offline. If a property list is online, it is associated with properties of a StorableObject or another property list. Any changes (additions, modifications, or removals) to the online property list are also reflected in the related objects. The example in C# demonstrates how to create and use both types of property lists.  

```csharp
// creation of persistent property list
FunctionPropertyList oPersistentPropertyList1 = oFunction.Properties;
oPersistentPropertyList1.FUNC_COMMENT = "Comment";
// now oFunction.Properties.FUNC_COMMENT is equal "Comment"
FunctionPropertyList oPersistentPropertyList2 = new FunctionPropertyList(oFunction);
oPersistentPropertyList2.FUNC_COMMENT = "Test";
// now oFunction.Properties.FUNC_COMMENT is equal "Test"
// creation of transient property list
FunctionPropertyList oTransientPropertyList = new FunctionPropertyList();
oTransientPropertyList.FUNC_COMMENT = "Test comment";
oFunction.Properties.FUNC_COMMENT = oTransientPropertyList.FUNC_COMMENT;
oTransientPropertyList.FUNC_COMMENT = "Transient comment";
// now oTransientPropertyList.FUNC_COMMENT is equal "Test comment"
```

```csharp
// Assuming 'oFunction' is an existing Function object

// creation of persistent property list
FunctionPropertyList oPersistentPropertyList1 = oFunction.Properties;
oPersistentPropertyList1.FUNC_COMMENT = "Comment";

// now oFunction.Properties.FUNC_COMMENT is equal "Comment"

FunctionPropertyList oPersistentPropertyList2 = new FunctionPropertyList(oFunction);
oPersistentPropertyList2.FUNC_COMMENT = "Test";

// now oFunction.Properties.FUNC_COMMENT is equal "Test"

// creation of transient property list
FunctionPropertyList oTransientPropertyList = new FunctionPropertyList();
oTransientPropertyList.FUNC_COMMENT = "Test comment";
oFunction.Properties.FUNC_COMMENT = oTransientPropertyList.FUNC_COMMENT;
oTransientPropertyList.FUNC_COMMENT = "Transient comment";

// now oTransientPropertyList.FUNC_COMMENT is equal "Test comment"
```

In this example:

*   `oPersistentPropertyList1` and `oPersistentPropertyList2` are persistent (online) lists. Changes to `FUNC_COMMENT` in these lists directly affect the `oFunction` object.
*   `oTransientPropertyList` is a transient (offline) list. Changes to `FUNC_COMMENT` in this list do *not* directly affect the `oFunction` object unless explicitly assigned (as shown in the example).

```csharp
// creation of persistent property list
FunctionPropertyList oPersistentPropertyList1 = oFunction.Properties;
oPersistentPropertyList1.FUNC_COMMENT = "Comment";
// now oFunction.Properties.FUNC_COMMENT is equal "Comment"
FunctionPropertyList oPersistentPropertyList2 = new FunctionPropertyList(oFunction);
oPersistentPropertyList2.FUNC_COMMENT = "Test";
// now oFunction.Properties.FUNC_COMMENT is equal "Test"
// creation of transient property list
FunctionPropertyList oTransientPropertyList = new FunctionPropertyList();
oTransientPropertyList.FUNC_COMMENT = "Test comment";
oFunction.Properties.FUNC_COMMENT = oTransientPropertyList.FUNC_COMMENT;
oTransientPropertyList.FUNC_COMMENT = "Transient comment";
// now oTransientPropertyList.FUNC_COMMENT is equal "Test comment"
```

